<div class="" id="index-dev-app-container">
    <h2>ADE-Enterprise ERP</h2>
    <a href="https://github.com/Marcel-harvey/ADE-Enterprise-ERP" target="_blank">Link to the GitHub Repo</a>

    <div class="image-container">
        <img />
    </div>

    <div class="">
        <h4>What does this app do?</h4>

        <p>
            This is a basic <a href="https://www.oracle.com/africa/erp/what-is-erp" target="_blank">ERP</a> (Enterprise Resource Planning) system designed to manage key business processes
            such as quotations, invoicing, purchase orders, and goods received notes. It also provides efficient inventory management by tracking stock levels and alerting users when quantities are
            low, ensuring timely restocking.

        </p>

        <p>
            The system leverages the Microsoft Identity Framework to manage user authentication and authorization, ensuring robust security and up-to-date account management. Role-based access control
            is implemented to define user permissions — for example, only administrators can create new users, while sales personnel are limited to creating quotes and invoices.
        </p>

        <p>
            In essence, this structure ensures that users operate within their designated roles, enhancing security, efficiency, and overall organizational control.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="">
        <h4>What is next / upgrades for this app</h4>

        <p>
            There are a couple of upgrades to still do on this app. 
            <br />
            To name a few:
            <ul class="stripped-list">
                <li>
                    Add proper payment methods to track when invoices are paid and what amount is paid. If it has been paid in full etc.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Add a stock taking method for if stock take is done.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Add a picking slipp function to the app so that you can have record of the picked stock and to who it weant.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

