    <div class="">
        <h4>What does this app do?</h4>

        <p>
            Lola Assistant was developed to streamline one of my primary gaming interfaces. While searching for a game, the application allowed me to select the desired game mode, choose my preferred role
            , and accept matches — all automatically — giving me the freedom to step away briefly (usually for a quick cup of coffee, an essential part of my personality).
        </p>

        <p>
            Lola was built using Python with AutoHotkey scripts to simulate mouse movements and clicks. Although this approach is somewhat outdated today, it proved highly effective at the time. The main limitation,
            however, was that the game interface had to remain in a fixed position on the screen for the automation to function correctly.
        </p>
    </div>

